nt of action plans for implementing sustainable pension strategies</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; margin-bottom: .0001pt; margin-left: .25in; text-indent: -.25in; line-height: 18.0pt; mso-list: l0 level1 lfo8; tab-stops: list .5in; background: white; border: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid #EEEEEE .75pt; padding: 0in; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 8.0pt 0in;\"><!-- [if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size: 10.0pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: Symbol; mso-fareast-font-family: Symbol; mso-bidi-font-family: Symbol; color: #222222;\"><span style=\"mso-list: Ignore;\">&middot;<span style=\"font: 7.0pt \'Times New Roman\';\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #222222;\">Closing remarks and acknowledgements</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt: auto; margin-bottom: .0001pt; line-height: normal; background: white;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12.0pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\',\'serif\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; color: #222222;\">This conference will offer a unique opportunity for attendees to gain insights, share experiences, and contribute to the development of strategies that promote the sustainability of pension systems in an ever-changing global landscape.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: .0001pt;\">&nbsp;</p>', '', 0, '', '9th-annual-pension-admin-conference-2024', '39493.JPG', 0, NULL, '2024-08-16 07:24:01', '2024-08-16 07:24:01'),
(19, 10, 'Developing Competent Skills in an E-library world', 'Business and Finance', 'workshop', '2024-08-20', '2024-08-22', 165000, 'NG', 'Maitama, Abuja', NULL, '', '<p>PROGRAM OBJECTIVE</p>\r\n<p>Rapid advances in information technologies have revolutionized the role of libraries. As a result, libraries face new challenges, competition, demands, and expectations. Libraries are redesigning services and information products to add value to their services and to satisfy the changing information needs of the user community. Traditional libraries are still handling largely printed materials that are expensive and bulky. Information seekers are no longer satisfied with only printed materials. They want to supplement the printed information with more dynamic electronic resources. Demands for digital information are increasing</p>\r\n<p>As a result of the new development and current needs, it is imperative that we equip the staffs of higher institutions to cope with challenges affecting e-libraries in higher institution.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>WORKSHOP PROFILE<br>1. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Library Automation and Use of Open Source Software</p>\r\n<p>2. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Using Online Classification Scheme and Online Catalogues in Cataloguing Information Materials</p>\r\n<p>3. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Indexing and Abstracting of Information Resources: The Role of Modern Technology</p>\r\n<p>4. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Developing Specialized Databases Usage Skills for Academic Research</p>\r\n<p>5. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Developing skills for deployment of Mobile technologies in libraries</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>WHO SHOULD ATTEND<br>Librarians, Library Officers, Lecturers, ICT staff etc in Universities, Polytechnics and Colleges of Education</p>', '', 0, '', 'developing-competent-skills-in-an-e-library-world', '82689.jpg', 0, NULL, '2024-08-16 07:37:34', '2024-08-16 07:37:34'),
(20, 10, 'Digital Marketing Strategies for Beating Competitors with 100 Times your spending Power', 'Business and Finance', 'workshop', '2024-11-05', '2024-11-07', 175000, 'NG', 'Maitama, Abuja', NULL, '', '<h3>Details</h3>\r\n<p>No matter what your industry is, or what products and services you offer - digital marketing trends cannot be ignored. Not so long ago, companies needed little more than a website and a Facebook page, but now, the digital landscape is evolving so quickly that it&rsquo;s hard to keep up.</p>\r\n<p>By now, there aren&rsquo;t too many successful businesses that don&rsquo;t have an online presence. Every year, new technologies and tools come to the fore, forcing marketers to adapt to keep their organizations at the top. If your organization fail to adapt and innovate to new technology annually you are likely to lag over time... Your productivity will slack.</p>\r\n<p class=\"\\\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Course outline</strong></p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Digital marketing trends that can enhance your business performance</p>\r\n<p class=\"\\\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Digital advertising marketing strategy</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;marketing strategy to help you get digital advertising results</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Nature of Digital Marketing &ndash; Characteristics of the medium</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Digital Marketing Mix</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How To Get Targeted Prospective&nbsp; Names, Emails and Specialization/Positions.</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Testing For Duplication of Emails.</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How To Verify Emails.</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Removing clients from the prospect list.</p>\r\n<p>&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;How to forward emails with an image using webmail</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<h3><strong>Who Is Right For The Program</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"\\\">This&nbsp;<strong>course</strong>&nbsp;is&nbsp;designed to meet the needs of all staff in your organisation who desire to learn new trends in digital marketing for beating competitors</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Methodology</strong></h3>\r\n<p>Interactive presentation, using practical exercises, demonstration, quizzes, hands-on group discussion, question and answer.&nbsp;&nbsp;role plays and case studies, participants in this course will gain useful insight into how to identify and use the attitudes and behaviours that have a positive impact on increased productivity</p>', '', 0, '', 'digital-marketing-strategies-for-beating-competitors-with-100-times-your-spending-power', '21560.JPG', 0, NULL, '2024-08-16 07:44:14', '2024-08-16 07:44:14'),
(21, 10, '12TH ANNUAL E-LIBRARY MANAGEMENT CONFERENCE 2024', 'Business and Finance', 'workshop', '2024-09-17', '2024-09-20', 105000, 'NG', 'Onipanu, Lagos', NULL, '', '<h3><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman;\"><strong><span data-darkreader-inline-color=\"\">Theme:&nbsp;</span></strong></span><strong>\"Empowering Knowledge: Unlocking the Potential of E-Libraries through Accessibility, Inclusivity, and User-Centric Design\"</strong></h3>\r\n<h3><strong>Conference Overview:</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The conference will address the current challenges and opportunities related to e-libraries. It will also highlight the importance of accessibility, inclusivity, and user-centric design in catering to diverse user needs and ensuring equal access to knowledge and information.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The conference will feature renowned experts, researchers, and practitioners in the field of e-libraries. Promote their expertise and the unique insights they will share, ensuring attendees gain valuable knowledge and stay updated with the latest trends and best practices.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Benefits of Attending the Conference:</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Interactive Workshops and Demonstrations: The conference will offer interactive workshops and demonstrations focused on practical implementation and showcasing innovative solutions. Attendees will have the opportunity to learn hands-on techniques, explore new technologies, and exchange ideas with peers.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Networking and Collaboration: the networking opportunities available at the conference, where attendees can connect with fellow professionals, exchange experiences, and build collaborative relationships. There will be great potential for future partnerships and knowledge sharing among participants.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Conference Content:</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 1: Opening Remarks and Introduction</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Conference Theme: Introduction</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Importance of accessibility, inclusivity, and user-centric design in E-Libraries</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Insights into the current landscape and future trends in E-Libraries</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 2: Understanding User Needs</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;User research and needs analysis for designing inclusive E-Libraries</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Creating user personas to guide design decisions</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 3: User-Centric Design Principles</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Principles of user-centric design in the context of digital libraries</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Design thinking methodologies for E-Library development</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 4: Inclusive Technologies and Tools</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Showcase technologies promoting inclusivity in E-Libraries</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Practical demonstrations of assistive technologies</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 5: Accessible Content Creation</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Guidelines for creating accessible digital content</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ensuring compatibility with assistive technologies</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 6: Case Studies in Inclusive E-Libraries</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Showcase of successful E-Library implementations with a focus on inclusivity</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Lessons learned and best practices from different organizations</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 7: Roundtable Discussion on Accessibility Challenges</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Interactive discussion on challenges faced in making E-Libraries accessible</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strategies for overcoming common barriers</p>\r\n<h3>This conference serves as a platform for professionals and enthusiasts in the library and information sciences to collaboratively explore ways to create digital library spaces that are accessible, inclusive, and user-centric.</h3>\r\n<h3><strong>ACCOMMODATION</strong>:&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">This conference is non-residential. Participants are to lodge in hotels of their choice near the Training centre. A list of these Hotels will be provided on request.&nbsp;</p>', '', 0, '', '12th-annual-e-library-management-conference-2024', '50409.JPG', 0, NULL, '2024-08-16 07:49:45', '2024-08-16 07:49:45'),
(22, 10, '11th ANNUAL LABOUR AND TRADE UNION CONFERENCE 2024', 'Business and Finance', 'workshop', '2024-08-20', '2024-08-23', 100500, 'NG', 'Maitama, Abuja', NULL, '', '<h3><strong>Conference Theme:&nbsp;</strong><strong>\"Building a Stronger Future: Uniting Labour Unions for Economic Resilience and Growth\"</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>Conference Overview:</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The conference addresses the current challenges and opportunities faced by labour unions in contributing to economic resilience. It will highlight the importance of collaboration, adaptability, and embracing new opportunities in navigating an ever-changing economic landscape.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">It will provide opportunities for engaging discussions, workshops, and interactive sessions. Attendees will have the chance to exchange ideas, share best practices, and learn from peers and industry experts.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">There will be networking opportunities available at the conference, where attendees can connect with labour union representatives, industry professionals, policymakers, and economic experts. Highlight the potential for collaboration, knowledge sharing, and building relationships that can contribute to collective success.</p>\r\n<h3><strong>Conference Content:</strong></h3>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 1: Introduction</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Introduction to the conference theme</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Overview of the importance of labour resilience in economic contexts</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Insights into current trends, challenges, and opportunities</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 2: Understanding Economic Challenges</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Analysis of economic challenges impacting the labour force</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Global and local economic trends affecting job markets</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 3: Labour Market Dynamics</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Examination of current labour market dynamics</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Shifting employment patterns and the gig economy</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 4: Building Individual and Collective Resilience</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strategies for individual career resilience</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Collective bargaining and labour union resilience</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 5: Embracing Technological Advancements</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Impacts of technological advancements on labour</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Navigating automation and embracing digital skills</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 6: Entrepreneurship and Job Creation</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Exploring entrepreneurship as a resilience strategy</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Job creation initiatives and success stories</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Session 7: Future-Proofing the Workforce</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Preparing the workforce for future challenges</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&middot;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Strategies for continuous learning and adaptation.</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Download Conference Flyer&nbsp;&nbsp;https://centreforproductivity.org/files/LABOUR-CONFERENCE-2024.pdf</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\">&nbsp; &nbsp; Download Special Invitation Letter&nbsp; https://centreforproductivity.org/files/SPECIAL-INVITE-TO-ANNUAL-LABOURTRADE-UNION-CONFERENCE.docx</p>', '', 0, '', '11th-annual-labour-and-trade-union-conference-2024', '50697.JPG', 0, NULL, '2024-08-16 07:54:09', '2024-08-16 07:54:09'),
(23, 10, 'Port Facility Security Officers Course', 'Business and Finance', 'workshop', '2024-09-17', '2024-09-19', 175000, 'NG', 'Onipanu, Lagos', NULL, '', '<h3>Details</h3>\r\n<div class=\"\\\">\r\n<div>\r\n<p>This intensive certified course is designed to give delegates a full understanding and competence to perform the duties and responsibilities of a Port Facility Security Officer (PFSO).</p>\r\n<p>This intensive certified course is designed to give delegates a full understanding and competence to perform the duties and responsibilities of a Port Facility Security Officer (PFSO). In particular the PFSO duties and responsibilities with respect to the security of a port facility, the actions following on from a Port Security Assessment, the development of, implementing, maintaining and updating of a Port Facility Security Plan (PFSP) and the requirements for liaising with Department of Transport and Tourism officials, Ship Security officers (SSOs) and Company Security Officers (CSOs).&nbsp;</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 0, '', 'port-facility-security-officers-course', '21529.JPG', 0, NULL, '2024-08-16 08:02:08', '2024-08-16 08:02:08');
